text.paragraph:
The recommended starting dose of almotriptan malate tablets in patients with hepatic impairment is 6.25 mg. The maximum daily dose should not exceed 12.5 mg over a 24-hour period [see Warnings and Precautions (

                              5.9

                           ) and Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].

The recommended starting dose of almotriptan malate tablets in patients with severe renal impairment is 6.25 mg. The maximum daily dose should not exceed 12.5 mg over a 24-hour period [see Warnings and Precautions (

                              5.9

                           ) and Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].

Because almotriptan malate may increase blood pressure, do not use almotriptan malate tablets in patients with uncontrolled hypertension [see Warnings and Precautions (

                              5.7

                           )].

